Azerbaijan expects a 12 percent
increase in natural-gas production by 2015, the Trend news
agency said, citing State Oil Co. of Azerbaijan documents.  Gas output will be 29 billion cubic meters, above the 25.8
billion the nation produced last year, the report said. Just
over 21 billion cubic meters will be provided by the BP Plc-led
Shah Deniz and Azeri-Chirag-Guneshli fields in Azerbaijanâ€™s
section of the Caspian Sea, while the state-run  oil company ,
known as Socar, will pump 7.9 billion cubic meters, it said.  Azerbaijan, the third-largest oil producer in the former
 Soviet Union  after Russia and Kazakhstan, produced 45.6 million
metric tons of oil last year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
